title: CPaaS SDK for business communication solutions | Rainbow
metaDescription: Add chat, conference, real time collaboration and communication (PBX, VoIP, P2P) capabilities, bots and more to your business applications.
mainHtml:
Documentation

SDK and server errors

LTS release 2.6.XPubli√©e le 2021-12-13

Errors list

Most of SDK methods use SdkResult<T> object to provide a result or the reason of the error

If no error occurs SdkResult<T>.Result.Succcess is equals to True. In this case SdkResult<T>.Data contains an object on T type.

If an error occurs SdkResult<T>.Result.Succcess is equals to False. To get information about the error the SdkResult<T>.Result (which is a SdkError object) cand be used.

There is three type of SdkError - see SdkErrorType:

  • SdkErrorType.NoError: There is no error. You have to use SdkResult<T>.Data
  • SdkErrorType.Exception: An unexpected exception has occurred. To have more information readable information use SdkError.ToString() or use SdkError.Exception object
  • SdkErrorType.IncorrectUse: The way to use the method is not done correctly (network error, server errors, or sdk errors - like invalid parameter). In this case properties you can use ErrorCode, ErrorDetailsCode, ErrorDetails and ErrorDetailsData of the object SdkError.IncorrectUseError for more information.

if SdkErrorType.IncorrectUse.ErrorCode is equals to 1000, it means that the SDK itself has raised an error.

For other values, it means that the Rainbowserver has raised an error.

Find below a full list of potential errors returned by the SDK or by the server.

In this case SdkResult<T>.Data contains an object on T type. If an error occurs SdkResult<T>.Result.Succcess is equals to False. To get information about the error the SdkResult<T>.Result (which is a SdkError object) cand be used. There is three type of SdkError - see SdkErrorType: SdkErrorType.NoError: There is no error. You have to use SdkResult<T>.Data SdkErrorType.Exception: An unexpected exception has occurred. To have more information readable information use SdkError.ToString() or use SdkError.Exception object SdkErrorType.IncorrectUse: The way to use the method is not done correctly (network error, server errors, or sdk errors - like invalid parameter). In this case properties you can use ErrorCode, ErrorDetailsCode, ErrorDetails and ErrorDetailsData of the object SdkError.IncorrectUseError for more information. if SdkErrorType.IncorrectUse.ErrorCode is equals to 1000, it means that the SDK itself has raised an error. For other values, it means that the Rainbowserver has raised an error. Find below a full list of potential errors returned by the SDK or by the server.
